{"url": "https://people.com/style/robert-de-niro-platform-shoes-al-pacino-the-irishman/", "text": "Robert De Niro will be towering over Al Pacino in their upcoming mobster film The Irishman thanks to a little movie magic.\n\nIn December, the two Oscar winners were photographed on the New York City set of the 2019 Martin Scorsese flick \u2014 with De Niro, 74, wearing lifts (to put it nicely) in his shoes to give him some height over Pacino, 77.\n\nThe move has nothing to do with vanity and everything to do with the fact that De Niro's character, hitman Frank \"The Irishman\" Sheeran, stood tall at 6-ft-4-in. Before his death in 2003, the alleged Bufalino crime family member claimed to have killed Teamster leader Jimmy Hoffa (played by Pacino) on the orders of mob boss Russell Bufalino.\n\nDe Niro confirmed that the height difference was the reason for the towering platforms on the Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon in April, saying they made the shoes to give him more inches in height. \"The guy [Sheeran] was actually much taller \u2014 about five, six inches taller than me \u2014 so [the shoes] were to show the relation to any of the other actors or characters that I'm taller.\"\n\nAuthor Charles Brandt detailed Sheeran's deathbed confession about Hoffa in the 2004 non-fiction book I Heard You Paint Houses, from which screenwriter Steven Zaillian adapted The Irishman's story.\n\nBACKGRID\n\nBACKGRID\n\nIn addition to his platform shoes, De Niro also wore a royal blue trench coat over a white collared shirt and dark slacks. He added a brown tie with diagonal stripes.\n\nPacino was costumed in a grey trench coat with coordinating pants. He also wore a white shirt with a red tie.\n\nThis is the fourth time De Niro and Pacino have worked together. They previously costarred in 2008's Righteous Kill, 1995's Heat and 1974's The Godfather Part II.\n\nIn addition to De Niro and Pacino, the movie will also star an out-of-retirement Joe Pesci (as Bufalino) as well as Harvey Keitel, Anna Paquin, Ray Romano and Bobby Cannavale.\n\nThe Irishman hits theaters in 2018.\n\nSaveSave", "images": ["https://people.com/thmb/2AIcBhhQ7tz0LVSuSIHXB91IaZw=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/al-pacino-robert-deniro-moncler-1-101425-c965f39446d343968f761cbc00cb2656.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/LztNjwaQ-ix4eK4edUooLhNiWi4=/800x533/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/anna-kepner-3-111025-c6a90b2f57474459a89ae04e296ec343.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/AGTNKYLijctZUMkSZI5F0Oa1nKI=/200x200/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/248515971_423792849226570_1672372709981615183_n-1e64af70e89941cfacf15401180d1334.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/BvzoaQFuTLVOFN4jzCOb-yYLg44=/343x228/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/meryl-streep-anne-hathaway-devil-wears-prada-2-111225-52cc2fdbefe24997ab2946c93fd4360f.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/h93Xi3GoAFbTuPZF4g5lIRnMZFU=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/David-Harbour-set-of-Evil-Genius-Stranger-Things-Premiere-111125-86de11f0f4b84ee9a6d46a723be0f313.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/ThfKECgcdqVcq1wKKEwWc0jV4nE=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/rose-byrne-bobby-cannavale-blue-moon-red-carpet-new-york-111025-0f22881adebc4e3393eb4b9e73819708.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/yaQNRQLFpzUDMYDuJjE4rWtE148=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/rosamund-pike-now-you-see-me-now-you-dont-photocall-2025-tom-cruise-tonight-show-110725-1eb2ea15417c42ed8cc54660c104d2a2.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/Vy8v6GABg2OEb0qJo4LVr-dhxkk=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/the-devil-wears-prada-meryl-streep-main-052325-0da30335c62b4364b569f818fb007db9.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/LfhGsq7KEjseX6u2wmLjW5D7KQ0=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Mel-Gibson-Kasia-Smutniak-102925-ab4d4e6ef63a4949aadd53e8a8e316da.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/0DLBfDRFo0ZZyhhpBweKX5tvrvg=/2